{{Infobox person
| name               = Prince Anahobe[[ja:穴穂部皇子]]
| birth_date         = Unknown
| birth_place        = [[Asuka]]
| death_date         = July 19, 587
| death_place        = [[Awaji]]
| title              = Imperial Prince
| mother             = Oanenokimi
| father             = [[Emperor Kinmei]]
}}
Prince Anahobe (穴穂部皇子) was a Japanese Prince.

He was born to Emperor Kinmei and a consort Oanenokimi, Anahobe would have been titled "Imperial Prince Anahobe"<ref name=":2">{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_oEfAAAAYAAJ |title=Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697 |date=1896 |publisher=Society |isbn=978-0-524-05347-8 |language=en}}</ref>

== Life == 
Not much is known about his early life. His life is mainly recorded from 585 onward when [[Emperor Bidatsu]] died. He was recorded saying, 'I don't understand why you obey the dead king and not the living one.'  <ref name=":2" />He wouldn't become Emperor despite effort as in October 585 [[Emperor Yomei|Prince Ōe]], would become the Emperor much to the prince's dismay. In May 586, Prince Anahobe tried to break into Hinkyu to rape [[Empress Suiko|Princess Nukatabe]], the widow of Emperor Bidatsu. He and many others described her as,  'fair of face and figure; well-mannered and polite.' As Anahobe tried break in [[Miwa no Sakau]], a favorite retainer of Emperor Bidatsu refused to let him in closing all the gates.<ref name=":2" /> Although Prince Anahobe called seven times at the gate, he still couldn't enter Hinkyu. He did complain to [[Soga no Umako]] stating Sakau was useless, this was an attempt to get him fired so that he could get to Nukatabe, Although this didn't work.<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=2023-05-06 |title=Soga Clan (蘇我氏) |url=https://jref.com/articles/soga-clan-%E8%98%87%E6%88%91%E6%B0%8F.646/ |access-date=2023-10-02 |website=Japan Reference |language=en-GB}}</ref> When Emperor Yomei was dying he wondered wether to practice Buddhism or not. While the [[Mononobe clan]] was anti Buddhist, [[Soga no Umako]] was pro Buddhist. He sent for Anahobe to get a Buddhist Priest named [[Toyokuni (Buddhist preist)|Toyokuni]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=The Story of Nun Zenshin-ni |url=http://asuka-japan-heritage.jp/global/en/zenshinni/life/p3.html |access-date=2023-10-02 |website=Exploring the Footsteps of the Heroines of Asuka |language=en}}</ref> In May 587, [[Mononobe no Moriya]] wanted to make Prince Anahobe the Emperor. This was due to Ōe's death. Moriya believed that Anahobe would be on the Shinto side.<ref name=":0" /> So he sent an agent to Prince Anahobe and asked him to come to [[Awaji]], pretending to go out for hunting. Soga no Umako caught wind of this. This would end the [[Soga–Mononobe conflict]] due to Umako sending assassins to kill Moriya, Prince Anahobe<ref name=":1" />, and [[Prince Yakabe]] an ally of Anahobe. When Moriya died Anahobe was defenceless. The assassin sent to kill Anahobe, climbed the tower Anahobe was on and cut his shoulder, Anahobe fell and died. The next day Yakabe also was killed.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" /><ref name="umehara">Takeshi Umehara , ''仏教の勝利'' (Tokyo: Shogakkan, 1980), 291-292.</ref>
== Soga & Mononobe clans ==
The clans of Mononobe and Soga attempted to win him over. Both wanted to make him Emperor. Umako sent Anahobe to get the Buddhist priest<ref name=":0" /> as a way to (in his eyes) possibly convert Anahobe. Yet the Mononobe sent for him to go "Fishing", this was an attempt at making him Emperor. This failed.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" />
==Ancestry==
